article.description: Josip Vrankic scored 17 points and Santa Clara never trailed in beating CSU Fullerton 70-55 Saturday night in the Cable Car Classic finale.
article.headline: Santa Clara top CSU Fullerton 70-55 in Cable Car Classic
article.linkText: Santa Clara top CSU Fullerton 70-55 in Cable Car Classic
article.story: SANTA CLARA, Calif. -- Josip Vrankic scored 17 points and Santa Clara never trailed in beating CSU Fullerton 70-55 Saturday night in the Cable Car Classic finale. DJ Mitchell scored 11 and grabbed seven rebounds and Tahj Eddy and Trey Wertz scored nine points apiece for the Broncos (8-1), who have won five straight. Guglielmo Caruso scored seven points in Santa Clara's opening 16-0 run and the Broncos led 42-19 at halftime and by as many as 23 points. Brandon Kamga scored 18 points and Austen Awosika added 12 for the Titans (3-5). Santa Clara plays at Nevada on Wednesday and CSU Fullerton plays at Pacific on Wednesday. --- More AP college basketball: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and https://twitter.com/AP-Top25
